(
  'Bill Clinton — Former U.S. President and Epstein Flight Network',
  'The Bill Clinton archive entry centers on former President William J. Clinton and his documented travel with Jeffrey Epstein. Flight logs and related investigative materials released under the Epstein Files Transparency Act show Clinton flew on Epstein''s private aircraft multiple times between 2002 and 2003. Court-admissible records and congressional references place Clinton in Epstein''s social circle during this period.',
  E'Documented Evidence Includes:\n\n• Epstein flight logs listing Clinton as a passenger on at least four flights in 2002–2003.\n• Photographs and witness statements released in 2025–2026 DOJ batches referencing Clinton''s travel and interactions.\n• Internal investigative memos and congressional records noting Clinton''s association with Epstein.\n• 2025–2026 Epstein Files releases containing additional travel records and correspondence.\n\nSignificant portions of the releases remain redacted for victim protection. These primary materials document elite political connections to the Epstein network.\n\nThe full searchable archive is publicly hosted by the Department of Justice at justice.gov/epstein and is updated as additional materials are identified.\n\nPrimary Sources (MLA Format)\n\nUnited States. Department of Justice. Epstein Library. www.justice.gov/epstein. Accessed 24 Mar. 2026.\n\nUnited States. Congress. House Oversight Committee. References to Clinton in Epstein Flight Logs. H. Rept. 119-468, 119th Congress, 2026.\n\nUnited States. Department of Justice. "Department of Justice Publishes 3.5 Million Responsive Pages in Compliance with the Epstein Files Transparency Act." 30 Jan. 2026, www.justice.gov/opa/pr/department-justice-publishes-35-million-responsive-pages-compliance-epstein-files.',
